  <TITLE>Static Analysis API to get scan status</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>It will be nice to have an API to get if a scan has been completed or not. **Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.** Right now the only way to know if a scan is complete or not is requesting a scan and seeing if there are any results. This is not best practice because this can trigger a new scan (even if re_scan parameter is set to 0). The scans API is not good either: it's not possible to know if the data is not available because the scan is not completed or because the scan is not started. **Describe the solution you'd like** A new API api/v1/scan_status that given the scan hash reply with a json containing two fields scanStarted and scanCompleted. The first one will be true if the scan has been started and the other one will be true if the scan has been completed. **Describe alternatives you've considered** Add the field scanStarted to scans API result json, so one can know why the scan data is not yet available</DESCRIPTION>
